UI Events:
---------
UI events include focus, scroll, resize, input, load, and others triggered by user interface changes.
scroll - User scrolls
resize -	Window resizes

Mouse Events:
--------------
Triggered when user interacts with mouse or touchpad.
click -	Single click
dblclick	- Double click
mousedown / mouseup -	Press / release mouse button

Moving the Mouse (mouseover/out, mouseenter/leave) -> Track when the mouse enters or leaves an element.

Drag and Drop (with mouse events) -> Browser supports drag-and-drop using dragstart, dragover, drop.

Pointer Events -> Unified events for mouse, touch, and stylus input.
pointerdown, pointerup, pointermove, pointerenter, pointerleave
Include properties like pointerId, pointerType (mouse, pen, touch)

Keyboard Events:
---------------
Listen for keyboard input using keydown and keyup.

keydown -	When key pressed (repeat fires if held)
keyup -	When key released

Scrolling:
----------
Fired when the page or element is scrolled.
Optimize scroll handlers (use debounce or requestAnimationFrame to avoid lag).
